            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where SEO.AI wins:</strong> if your job is research, competitive analysis, or running a multi-client agency — SEO.AI earns its keep. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your job is growing organic traffic without hiring a content team. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is SEO.AI?</h2>
        <p>SEO.AI is a done-for-you AI SEO platform built to automate the full content pipeline: keyword gap analysis, publication planning, article writing, internal linking, image generation, and direct CMS publishing.</p>

        <p>The core mechanism: SEO.AI scans your site against competitors, identifies keyword gaps, builds a content plan, writes long-form articles (2,000–5,000+ words) with Brand Voice calibration, generates featured images, inserts internal links, and pushes to your CMS automatically. The CMS coverage is the broadest in the category — <strong>WordPress, Webflow, Shopify, Wix, Squarespace, Magento, plus custom webhook</strong>.</p>

        <p>What SEO.AI <em>does not</em> do: no Google Business Profile management, no Map Pack tracking, no technical SEO audits, no backlink analysis, no rank tracking dashboard, no social media posting. It is a content automation product — period.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">Company background</div>
          <p>2022, founded by Torbjørn Flensted and Daniel Højris Bæk in <strong>Kongens Lyngby, Denmark</strong>. The founding team brings 20+ years of combined SEO agency experience. Small (11–50 employees per LinkedIn), independently funded, no disclosed external investment. The product is built around one bet — that SMBs need SEO content at volume but cannot justify a $1,000–$5,000/mo agency retainer.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">SEO.AI features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is broad. Here is what actually matters in daily use, broken down by module.</p>

        <h3>1. Content Gap Analysis</h3>
        <p>Scans your site against competitors and surfaces topics you do not cover. Output is a prioritised article list with keyword targets and topic clusters already applied — genuinely the hardest part of the workflow for most SMB owners.</p>

        <h3>2. AI Article Writing</h3>
        <p>Long-form SEO articles (2,000–5,000+ words) structured around target keywords and SERP research. Brand Voice configuration accepts 2–3 example pieces so the AI calibrates to your tone. Users consistently cite this as the feature that separates SEO.AI from generic AI writers.</p>

        <h3>3. Internal Linking</h3>
        <p>Automatically inserts internal links between articles using semantic relevance — no manual mapping. Works retroactively when new content is published.</p>

        <h3>4. AI Image Generation</h3>
        <p>Featured images generated per article. Quality is roughly Midjourney v5-era — fine for blog posts, not magazine-grade.</p>

        <h3>5. Direct CMS Publishing</h3>
        <p>Native publishing to WordPress, Webflow, Shopify, Wix, Squarespace, Magento, plus a custom webhook. Modes: Auto-Publish, Requires Approval (drafts), or Schedule. <strong>Shopify and Wix support is unique</strong> — no direct competitor matches this breadth.</p>

        <h3>6. Teammate Autopilot</h3>
        <p>On the Teammate tier, the system runs the entire monthly SEO workflow without ongoing input. Gap analysis → content planning → writing → linking → publishing. Output cadence: 1–2 articles per week (4–8/mo). Not a hard guarantee.</p>

        <h3>7. What is missing</h3>
        <p>No Google Business Profile, no Local SEO, no technical site audits, no backlink analysis, no rank tracking dashboard, no social media posting. If you need any of these, you will bolt on another tool.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">SEO.AI pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>SEO.AI publishes pricing. Most reviews quote the sticker. We will quote the <em>full</em> cost — sticker plus everything you have to bolt on to actually publish content.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>What you get</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Self-Serve Basic</strong></td><td>$149</td><td>$89</td><td>1 site · AI writer + research</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Self-Serve Pro</strong></td><td>$299</td><td>$179</td><td>Multi-site · Brand Voice · Bulk</td></tr>
